  "original_title": "\u0dbd\u0dd2\u0da7\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0ddd \u0d9c\u0dd1\u0dc3\u0dca \u0db8\u0dd2\u0dbd \u0dbb\u0dd4 50\u0d9a\u0dd2\u0db1\u0dca \u0d89\u0dc4\u0dc5\u0da7",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Liter gas price up by Rs 50",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Litro Company has increased the price of its domestic 12.5 kg gas cylinder by 50 rupees. Accordingly, the price of a gas cylinder in Colombo district will increase to 4910 rupees.",
        "Meanwhile, after a few weeks, Litro Company has resumed gas distribution from today. Yesterday, with the arrival of a ship carrying gas in Sri Lanka, the gas distribution activities have started.",
        "Today, gas is distributed only to Colombo and its suburbs. The distribution of gas to outside provinces is scheduled to start from tomorrow.",
        "Also, the company informs to avoid unnecessary stockpiling and that gas will be provided only after submitting the May electricity bill.",
        "The list of gas distribution points is to be published through the company's website and through social media."
      ],
